<br>
Delilah sprinkled  handful of a mixture of herbs into her cauldron, the once brown-looking potion now turning red. While making her potion, her mind was thinking about things that she was hearing about within the Amazon Lands.<br>
<br>
These petty things about Dawn... The amazons's hate for the gods.. I mean, if they hate all gods as many keep generally pointing out, Delilah wondered what good she would be able to do for this Amazon Nation, seeing as she was a goddess and an Amazon queen, with a rightfully earned title as one.<br>
<br>
She wondered if that many of the Amazons knew who exactly she was... a goddess. She wondered what their response would be.<br>
<br>
A hand reached into a cage at her side and she pulled out a venomous snake, stroking it idly with the other hand as the wooden spoon of her cauldon stirred on it's own. She then grasped it tightly until it suffocated from a lack of air as she muttered a few ritualistic words under her breath.<br>
<br>
Once the snake had died, she held the snake around the head with both hands and dug her nails into the skull, cracking it and breaking it into two. She then tore the snake into two halves with her hands and dumped one half in and the eyeball and fangs of the other half in as well, discarding what was left.  The potion was now yellow.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh well.. I won't give up trying..&quot; she muttered as she did a little hand-waving and jarred her new potion in a large, red glass container and all her instrument vanished. &quot;That's all for the night.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
She dusted off her hands and pulled her hair back, tying it with a stretch of cloth. &quot;Now time to catch that annoying little sprite in the forest...&quot; She turned around and walked straight into the forest, heading toward the center.<br>
<br>
<br>
~*Delilah Melpomene Tragedy*~<br>
